description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are an enthusiastic mental health nurse interested in working with older people who have a range of mental health conditions this may be the post for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ARU is piloting a seven day service within its unit – uniting ARU and React as a new enhanced service model in order to provide high intensity, recovery focused assessments and interventions for community dwelling older people, that previously may have required hospital admission, as well as supporting early discharge from our wards for those people who would benefit from this service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a minimum of 6 months post qualifying and have completed your Foundation Programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will include opportunities for personal and professional development in relation to multi-disciplinary teamwork, assessment skills and person centred, crisis recovery focussed care and interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 17/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tina Taki&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: ARU Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Tina.taki@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02920 715644 &lt;/p&gt;
